{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GvhW359ceXS2WsnXvNAovS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good — fresh project, no `index.html` yet. Let me:\n\n1. Move the first task to \"In Progress\" in fix_plan.md\n2. Create the `index.html` file\n\nLet me read the task description again carefully:\n\n> Create `index.html`: semantic HTML structure (`<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<article>`), viewport meta, two `<meta name=\"theme-color\">` tags (light + dark), description meta, preconnect to `api.github.com` + `fonts.googleapis.com` + `fonts.gstatic.com`, Google Fonts link (Source Serif 4 weights 300/400/600/700/italic + Inter 400/500), skip-to-content link, link to `css/style.css`, script module `js/app.js`. \n\nNow I'm checking the specs to get the exact values — the theme colors are #f8f6f1 for light and #1a1916 for dark, and I need to pull the full Google Fonts URL with the specific font weights and variants for both Source Serif 4 and Inter.\n\nLooking at the page structure, I have two main screens to build: the repo index with a hero section and list, and the commit reader with navigation and a reading progress bar. I need to figure out what stays static in the HTML versus what gets rendered dynamically by the JavaScript module.\n\nSetting up the HTML document... Building the HTML structure... I'm realizing that having two `<main>` elements violates HTML5 semantics, so I need to reconsider the structure—maybe using a single `<main>` that switches between views, or wrapping each view's content differently to maintain valid markup while keeping the semantic hierarchy intact. I'm settling on a practical structure where the main content area wraps the repo list, with the hero section sitting above it in the repo view, and the reader view toggling separately below—this keeps the semantic HTML clean while allowing both views to coexist without violating the single visible `<main>` rule. I'm finalizing the HTML structure for the reader view and now updating the task status in the plan document to mark this work as in progress.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":305,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4534,"cache_read_input_tokens":32693,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4534},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"27f9d074-e552-4076-906c-5830713f721a","uuid":"e38744dc-4ebb-4a3b-9a2a-c867d5384f09"}
