{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GwHuwTVw6yCDXpFHgDLgBS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that the repo-view isn't being hidden when navigating to the reader. This is because the transition code expects `currentView === 'repo'` to fade out repo view, but on initial load `currentView` is null, so it doesn't fade out the repo view. Let me debug this.\n\nWhen navigating directly to `/#/repo/linux`:\n1. First, `route()` is called from the initial load\n2. `hash` is `#/repo/linux`\n3. `cleanupReader()` is called\n4. `transitionViews(readerView, currentView === 'reader' ? readerView : null)` — wait, currentView is null, so `outgoing` is null\n\n\n5. So readerView gets shown, but repoView is never hidden because it wasn't passed as the outgoing view\n\nThe real problem is that repoView starts visible in the HTML with no hidden attribute, while readerView has one. When transitioning directly to the reader on initial load, I need to explicitly hide the repo view since it's not being treated as the outgoing view.\n\nThe fix is to always hide whichever view we're leaving, regardless of whether there's a previous view to transition from.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1838,"cache_read_input_tokens":103676,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1838},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"27f9d074-e552-4076-906c-5830713f721a","uuid":"11ec5c47-438d-404c-8353-6bd55e5049fe"}
